P1 - Disk Full Incident
Overview

This project simulates a Linux disk full incident and demonstrates how to investigate and resolve the issue.

The lab environment uses Ubuntu running in VirtualBox.

Problem

The system ran out of disk space and returned the error:

No space left on device
Simulation

Check disk usage:

df -h

Create large files to fill disk space:

fallocate -l 18G bigfile1
fallocate -l 2G bigfile2

Trigger disk full:

dd if=/dev/zero of=triggerfile bs=100M status=progress
Investigation

Find large files:

du -ah . | sort -rh | head

Example result:

19G ./bigfile1
2.1G ./bigfile2
1.1G ./triggerfile
Resolution

Remove the large files:

rm bigfile1 bigfile2 triggerfile

Verify disk space recovery:

df -h
Evidence

Terminal log:

terminal.log

Screenshots:

screenshots/
